111
00:06:23,880 --> 00:06:26,240
I think that's true in finance too.

112
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:28,680
The best example is the industry cycle.

113
00:06:29,910 --> 00:06:30,910
If you look at the big picture,

114
00:06:31,430 --> 00:06:33,310
the subprime crisis isn't over yet.

115
00:06:34,240 --> 00:06:36,680
Coal prices went up earlier this year,

116
00:06:36,680 --> 00:06:39,200
but that wasn't just because of demand.

117
00:06:39,240 --> 00:06:41,430
Plus, the ChiNext Board is opening soon,

118
00:06:41,430 --> 00:06:42,400
and new energy concept stocks

119
00:06:42,400 --> 00:06:44,880
will attract more investors
as growth stocks.

120
00:06:46,200 --> 00:06:47,270
So overall, here's my take,

121
00:06:47,790 --> 00:06:50,240
the coal industry
is already in a downturn.

122
00:06:51,790 --> 00:06:53,840
While organizing Risheng's trading data,

123
00:06:54,150 --> 00:06:55,720
I focused mainly on resource stocks.

124
00:06:56,310 --> 00:06:57,240
Right now,

125
00:06:57,430 --> 00:06:59,880
