Suspecting a big gap
in Shanke's share price,

129
00:07:08,950 --> 00:07:10,680
I ran a modeling analysis on it.

130
00:07:10,840 --> 00:07:11,840
The results showed

131
00:07:12,270 --> 00:07:13,270
Shanke Coal's share price

132
00:07:13,270 --> 00:07:15,790
has seriously strayed
from Risheng's profit expectations.

133
00:07:16,270 --> 00:07:17,750
It's not a growth stock,

134
00:07:17,790 --> 00:07:20,840
and its corporate compound
growth rate can't hit 18%.

135
00:07:22,110 --> 00:07:23,040
So overall,

136
00:07:23,630 --> 00:07:25,880
before the market shows clear signs,

137
00:07:26,310 --> 00:07:28,630
now is the best time to sell Shanke.

138
00:07:29,750 --> 00:07:30,750
If you wait any longer,

139
00:07:30,750 --> 00:07:32,240
you might miss your chance to exit.

140
00:07:46,720 --> 00:07:49,000
I even printed out
my whole calculation process.

141
00:07:50,430 --> 00:07:53,080
I was going to submit this
after the interview.

142
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:55,720
I thought it would give me an edge.

143
00:07:56,200 --> 00:07:57,240
But now it seems

144
00:07:57,240 --> 00:07:58,630
