147
00:08:07,200 --> 00:08:08,240
Not exactly.

148
00:08:08,840 --> 00:08:11,430
I started
with the residual income model,

149
00:08:11,790 --> 00:08:14,040
then factored in the local market
and Shanke Coal,

150
00:08:14,040 --> 00:08:15,200
and built out an expanded version.

151
00:08:16,080 --> 00:08:18,910
Olson's theory has some assumptions.

152
00:08:19,680 --> 00:08:22,520
Are you that sure
about your calculations?

