00:15:29,990 --> 00:15:31,240
Why'd you bring back a chicken?

279
00:15:31,240 --> 00:15:32,350
Do you even know how to cook it?

280
00:15:32,350 --> 00:15:33,670
I'll just learn.

281
00:15:33,670 --> 00:15:35,080
Uncle, I've been thinking.

282
00:15:35,080 --> 00:15:37,470
From now on, I want to be a chef.

283
00:15:37,470 --> 00:15:39,150
So I need to pick up more skills, right?

284
00:15:40,040 --> 00:15:40,600
Oh, also,

285
00:15:41,080 --> 00:15:41,990
I've got this too.

286
00:15:42,400 --> 00:15:44,040
The owner of Fang Fei's gave it to me.

287
00:15:45,990 --> 00:15:46,990
It's the Secret Recipe for Chicken.

288
00:15:49,920 --> 00:15:50,950
Uncle,

289
00:15:50,950 --> 00:15:52,830
I heard everything you told me before.

290
00:15:52,990 --> 00:15:53,830
But honestly,

291
00:15:54,150 --> 00:15:55,720
I'm just not cut out for studying.

292
00:15:56,040 --> 00:15:57,600
Every time I try, I get sleepy.

293
00:15:57,600 --> 00:15:59,240
Seriously, every time.

294
00:15:59,470 --> 00:16:00,310
But,

295
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:02,920
cooking is something I really love.

296
00:16:02,920 --> 00:16:03,630
I mean it.

297
00:16:03,630 --> 00:16:05,400
I'll work hard with Fei.

298
00:16:05,630 --> 00:16:07,790
Someday, when I have money,
I'll open my own restaurant.

299
00:16:08,670 --> 00:16:09,400
Bao,

300
00:16:10,190 --> 00:16:11,630
you need to understand something.

301
00:16:12,720 --> 00:16:13,600
In fact,

302
00:16:14,400 --> 00:16:15,990
you aren't into cooking.

303
00:16:16,350 --> 00:16:18,470
You're just into eating, right?

304
00:16:18,560 --> 00:16:20,240
Eating and cooking don't clash.

305
00:16:24,040 --> 00:16:24,760
Uncle,

306
00:16:25,080 --> 00:16:26,400
how's your job search going?

307
00:16:26,400 --> 00:16:27,190
Any luck so far?

308
00:16:27,600 --> 00:16:29,190
I knew it at the interview.

309
00:16:29,670 --> 00:16:30,790
The things they said made it clear.

310
00:16:30,790 --> 00:16:32,240
How could they ever hire me?

311
00:16:32,350 --> 00:16:33,630
I checked the list. Not on it.

312
00:16:44,440 --> 00:16:45,040
It's fine,

313
00:16:45,040 --> 00:16:45,510
uncle.

314
00:16:46,150 --> 00:16:47,990
No one ever got stuck forever.

315
00:16:48,600 --> 00:16:49,400
If they won't take you,

316
00:16:49,400 --> 00:16:50,600
that's their loss.

317
00:16:51,630 --> 00:16:53,990
Actually, I don't want a job at Risheng.

318
00:16:54,600 --> 00:16:57,040
They've got info about Ke's mining.

319
00:16:57,040 --> 00:16:58,470
I just want to check their archives.

320
00:17:03,510 --> 00:17:04,760
If Risheng doesn't work out,

321
00:17:04,990 --> 00:17:06,990
I need to find a way
into Jufeng Capital.

322
00:17:08,350 --> 00:17:10,240
But they're not hiring publicly.

323
00:17:14,470 --> 00:17:15,350
It's okay, uncle.

324
00:17:16,470 --> 00:17:17,190
Keep moving forward.

325
00:17:18,040 --> 00:17:18,790
You taught me that.

326
00:17:20,280 --> 00:17:20,830
Uncle,

327
00:17:21,440 --> 00:17:23,240
did you reach out
to that girl we met last time?

328
00:17:23,600 --> 00:17:24,990
Isn't she also in Hang City?

329
00:17:24,990 --> 00:17:26,790
She seemed pretty generous last time.

330
00:17:26,830 --> 00:17:27,830
She must have some connections.

331
00:17:28,310 --> 00:17:29,510
Maybe she could help you out.

332
00:17:30,440 --> 00:17:31,440
I did reach out.

333
00:17:31,790 --> 00:17:32,400
She asked if I'd arrived yet.

334
00:17:32,760 --> 00:17:34,310
I told her I was quite busy right now.

335
00:17:34,310 --> 00:17:35,120
I can't really get away.

336
00:17:37,950 --> 00:17:38,760
What?

337
00:17:39,280 --> 00:17:40,080
Why?

338
00:17:44,150 --> 00:17:45,310
How should I put it?

339
00:17:46,350 --> 00:17:47,790
I just don't want to owe anyone a favor.

340
00:17:48,190 --> 00:17:50,600
Right now, all I care about is Ke.

341
00:17:51,400 --> 00:17:52,880
I don't have the energy
for anything else.

342
00:17:53,190 --> 00:17:54,190
Besides,

343
00:17:54,190 --> 00:17:55,560
look at how things are for me now,

344
00:17:56,150 --> 00:17:56,760
how am I

345
00:17:56,760 --> 00:17:58,600
supposed to meet anyone?
It's awkward.

346
00:17:59,400 --> 00:18:00,280
Uncle,

347
00:18:00,280 --> 00:18:02,240
you're really smart,

348
00:18:02,790 --> 00:18:04,440
but sometimes you overthink things.

349
00:18:06,510 --> 00:18:07,790
I can't help you with this one,

350
00:18:08,350 --> 00:18:08,990
and I don't even get

351
00:18:08,990 --> 00:18:09,990
what you're saying.

352
00:18:10,190 --> 00:18:11,400
You'll have to figure it out yourself.

353
00:18:12,080 --> 00:18:12,990
I'm off to make dinner.

354
00:18:19,320 --> 00:18:24,680
[Jufeng Capital]

355
00:18:30,600 --> 00:18:35,040
[Li Zhijin, the chairwoman
of Jufeng Capital]

356
00:18:44,920 --> 00:18:45,720
Good morning, Ms. Li.

357
00:18:46,240 --> 00:18:47,040
Good morning, Ms. Li.

358
00:18:50,280 --> 00:18:51,080
Ms. Li.

359
00:18:51,600 --> 00:18:52,990
Here's the latest updated proposal.

360
00:18:53,630 --> 00:18:54,440
Yesterday, I...

361
00:18:56,240 --> 00:18:57,310
Ms. Song.

362
00:18:57,470 --> 00:18:59,440
The Equity Investment Department
made a bad call,

363
00:18:59,510 --> 00:19:01,990
leading to a 2% drawdown
on our flagship product.

364
00:19:03,240 --> 00:19:04,190
What's your take on this?

365
00:19:06,560 --> 00:19:08,670
Ms. Li, I...

366
00:19:12,880 --> 00:19:13,920
I'll speak up.

367
00:19:19,190 --> 00:19:20,150
Jufeng Capital,

368
00:19:20,150 --> 00:19:22,560
at its core,
is all about talented people.

369
00:19:23,560 --> 00:19:24,630
Everyone here

370
00:19:25,400 --> 00:19:27,600
gets the highest pay in the business.

371
00:19:28,240 --> 00:19:30,350
So you need to deliver value
that matches it.

372
00:19:31,150 --> 00:19:32,190
But honestly,

373
00:19:32,880 --> 00:19:35,080
no one is irreplaceable here.

374
00:19:36,040 --> 00:19:37,150
I built Jufeng

375
00:19:38,760 --> 00:19:40,760
to lead this whole industry.

376
00:19:41,440 --> 00:19:43,150
If someone doesn't get that,

377
00:19:43,990 --> 00:19:45,600
then they're just not right
or this place.

378
00:19:52,880 --> 00:19:54,040
I've only got thirty minutes

379
00:19:54,040 --> 00:19:55,950
to hear your growth plan
for next quarter.

380
00:19:58,880 --> 00:19:59,790
Are you listening or not?

381
00:20:06,040 --> 00:20:07,280
I've got some inside info.

382
00:20:07,510 --> 00:20:08,190
Let's talk in person.

383
00:20:19,600 --> 00:20:22,310
Mr. Wei, my boss is really upset.

384
00:20:23,280 --> 00:20:25,080
The inspection by the coast guard

385
00:20:25,080 --> 00:20:26,760
already cost us quite a bit.

386
00:20:27,510 --> 00:20:29,400
Now you want more goods,

387
00:20:29,880 --> 00:20:32,510
it's hard for us to trust you again.

388
00:20:32,510 --> 00:20:34,310
I'm here to make it up to you.

389
00:20:35,760 --> 00:20:37,720
I know you pulled a big move.

390
00:20:38,950 --> 00:20:41,400
Now the international market
is watching oil closely,

391
00:20:42,080 --> 00:20:43,600
and you still went after the oil pipeline.

392
00:20:45,040 --> 00:20:45,920
You're eager to sell

393
00:20:46,240 --> 00:20:47,280
your goods on hand, right?

394
00:20:49,190 --> 00:20:50,350
You want to buy in...

395
00:20:54,600 --> 00:20:55,310
Make them quiet.

396
00:20:59,510 --> 00:21:00,310
Alright.

397
00:21:00,920 --> 00:21:03,790
But this time, no advance payment.

398
00:21:05,280 --> 00:21:06,760
Only full buyout works.

399
00:21:07,400 --> 00:21:08,190
US dollars.

400
00:21:10,310 --> 00:21:11,790
If you want the goods,

401
00:21:11,790 --> 00:21:12,670
pay it all at once.

402
00:21:18,720 --> 00:21:20,280
That's not how deals work.

403
00:21:21,950 --> 00:21:22,950
I paid the money.

404
00:21:23,760 --> 00:21:25,670
Then someone snatched
the goods right away.

405
00:21:27,350 --> 00:21:28,350
Stuff like that,

406
00:21:30,440 --> 00:21:31,990
I can only let it slide once.

407
00:21:37,040 --> 00:21:38,510
What the hell are you doing?

408
00:21:47,440 --> 00:21:48,350
Mr. Wei,

409
00:21:48,880 --> 00:21:52,790
you know I used to admire your smarts.

410
00:21:53,880 --> 00:21:55,600
But sometimes,

411
00:21:55,600 --> 00:21:59,240
being too clever isn't always good.

412
00:22:02,280 --> 00:22:04,150
I want 50,000 tons of refined oil.

413
00:22:04,150 --> 00:22:05,510
Buying it all is fine.

414
00:22:05,510 --> 00:22:07,150
But only at today's price.

415
00:22:08,150 --> 00:22:09,830
Or,

416
00:22:09,830 --> 00:22:11,310
we can stick to advance payments

417
00:22:11,310 --> 00:22:12,600
and split the profits thirty-seventy.

418
00:22:14,950 --> 00:22:17,120
You know finance is my real edge.

419
00:22:17,950 --> 00:22:19,150
Oil prices will go up for sure.

420
00:22:19,830 --> 00:22:22,470
I promise we'll make a real fortune.

421
00:22:24,280 --> 00:22:24,830
Twenty-eighty.

422
00:23:07,600 --> 00:23:10,150
You know the law here is strict.

423
00:23:13,630 --> 00:23:15,150
Smuggling is such a big risk.

424
00:23:16,510 --> 00:23:18,310
If you push harder,

425
00:23:18,310 --> 00:23:19,310
I'm out.

426
00:23:23,950 --> 00:23:26,150
This time, I trust you.

427
00:23:27,400 --> 00:23:31,120
But there can't be any mistakes.

428
00:23:31,560 --> 00:23:32,830
You know me.

429
00:23:34,990 --> 00:23:35,760
I'm not that brave.

430
00:23:35,760 --> 00:23:36,630
Don't scare me.

431
00:23:37,150 --> 00:23:37,630
Alright?

432
00:23:40,950 --> 00:23:41,470
Deal.

433
00:23:43,950 --> 00:23:45,280
Actually,

434
00:23:45,280 --> 00:23:46,760
there are more profitable things.

435
00:23:46,950 --> 00:23:48,120
You should give it a shot.

436
00:23:48,350 --> 00:23:50,600
Thanks, but I stay away from drugs.

437
00:24:02,120 --> 00:24:03,120
What's going on here?

438
00:24:03,310 --> 00:24:04,560
It's life or death, uncle.

439
00:24:05,120 --> 00:24:05,920
Is everyone okay?

440
00:24:06,280 --> 00:24:07,150
I'm fine.

441
00:24:07,510 --> 00:24:09,720
Don't use water! Where's the lid?

442
00:24:09,830 --> 00:24:10,720
Here.

443
00:24:11,830 --> 00:24:13,310
Go, open all the doors!

444
00:24:25,990 --> 00:24:27,280
Oh no, there's still a fire.

445
00:24:31,760 --> 00:24:33,120
Open all the doors outside.

446
00:24:54,950 --> 00:24:56,150
Did anyone ever do anything to you?

447
00:24:56,670 --> 00:24:58,350
You ruined a perfect chicken.

448
00:24:58,720 --> 00:24:59,720
Look what you did to it.

449
00:25:00,120 --> 00:25:00,920
Such a waste of food.

450
00:25:02,470 --> 00:25:03,310
Seriously,

451
00:25:03,560 --> 00:25:05,080
you aren't meant to be an employee.

452
00:25:05,310 --> 00:25:06,510
You know what you should do?

453
00:25:06,510 --> 00:25:08,190
You should open a restaurant.

454
00:25:08,470 --> 00:25:09,950
Cook every chicken just like this,

455
00:25:09,950 --> 00:25:11,120
and serve them to your customers

456
00:25:11,150 --> 00:25:12,120
one by one.

457
00:25:12,120 --> 00:25:13,040
Uncle.

458
00:25:13,040 --> 00:25:14,120
Uncle, that's enough.

459
00:25:14,990 --> 00:25:16,560
Let's just have instant noodles
for lunch.

460
00:25:16,880 --> 00:25:19,600
Sure, I'll clean up after lunch.

461
00:25:21,790 --> 00:25:22,600
Coming!

462
00:25:23,350 --> 00:25:24,150
I'll get it, let me.

463
00:25:31,670 --> 00:25:32,510
- Hello.
- Hi.

464
00:25:32,790 --> 00:25:33,240
Li Qian.

465
00:25:34,510 --> 00:25:36,350
I was going to call and meet you out.

466
00:25:37,280 --> 00:25:39,120
But I saw your address is close by.

467
00:25:39,240 --> 00:25:40,600
Somehow, I just ended up here.

468
00:25:40,600 --> 00:25:41,510
Is this too sudden?

469
00:25:42,120 --> 00:25:43,120
Not at all.

470
00:25:43,120 --> 00:25:43,920
Who is it?

471
00:25:45,670 --> 00:25:47,150
Come on, tidy up a bit.

472
00:25:47,560 --> 00:25:48,790
Hi, please come in.

473
00:25:53,630 --> 00:25:54,400
Make yourself at home.

474
00:25:59,080 --> 00:26:00,150
Let me get to the point.

475
00:26:00,470 --> 00:26:01,510
I'm here to see you.

476
00:26:01,510 --> 00:26:02,920
I want to invite you to join Risheng.

477
00:26:07,560 --> 00:26:08,920
I saw the list.

478
00:26:08,920 --> 00:26:09,720
Your name wasn't on it.

479
00:26:10,760 --> 00:26:12,600
We even had two meetings just for you.

480
00:26:12,600 --> 00:26:13,990
Still, we couldn't reach a decision.

481
00:26:16,310 --> 00:26:17,920
Your strengths really stand out.

482
00:26:18,600 --> 00:26:19,990
Strictly in terms of skills,

483
00:26:19,990 --> 00:26:22,080
you're beyond an ordinary trader.

484
00:26:26,120 --> 00:26:27,950
But your flaws are just as clear.

485
00:26:28,920 --> 00:26:30,470
Though, maybe "flaws" isn't fair.

486
00:26:30,920 --> 00:26:31,880
You've got an edge.

487
00:26:33,120 --> 00:26:35,670
But we're looking for staff,

488
00:26:35,670 --> 00:26:37,600
not someone to boss us around.

489
00:26:43,920 --> 00:26:45,760
Honestly, what you said is true.

490
00:26:45,760 --> 00:26:46,920
I can't promise that'll change.

491
00:26:47,720 --> 00:26:49,240
Because in my view,

492
00:26:49,240 --> 00:26:50,400
doing the right thing

493
00:26:50,470 --> 00:26:52,190
matters way more than saving face.

494
00:26:57,560 --> 00:26:59,510
For you, following orders strictly

495
00:26:59,510 --> 00:27:00,600
just means saving face.

496
00:27:00,600 --> 00:27:01,920
I'm honestly not surprised.

497
00:27:02,950 --> 00:27:04,920
If that's the case,

498
00:27:05,560 --> 00:27:06,920
maybe starting a business

499
00:27:07,510 --> 00:27:09,310
is the only real option for you.

500
00:27:12,280 --> 00:27:13,150
This company

501
00:27:13,150 --> 00:27:13,950
or the whole society,

502
00:27:14,150 --> 00:27:15,720
has levels for a reason.

503
00:27:15,790 --> 00:27:17,510
It's to keep order
and set responsibility.

504
00:27:18,150 --> 00:27:20,950
After all, the world
isn't about truth alone.

505
00:27:21,880 --> 00:27:24,190
It's here for people
from all walks of life,

506
00:27:24,190 --> 00:27:25,920
so everyone can be a part
of how it runs.

507
00:27:25,920 --> 00:27:27,510
I see that differently.

508
00:27:28,470 --> 00:27:29,280
Have some water.

509
00:27:31,830 --> 00:27:32,470
When I was a kid,

510
00:27:32,470 --> 00:27:33,510
my grandpa taught me

511
00:27:34,470 --> 00:27:35,560
everyone needs something to hold on to.

512
00:27:35,760 --> 00:27:37,040
That's how you grow.

513
00:27:38,120 --> 00:27:39,950
That applies here too, I think.

514
00:27:40,830 --> 00:27:43,400
If you know an order is wrong,

515
00:27:43,510 --> 00:27:45,560
but don't stand up due to rank.

516
00:27:46,400 --> 00:27:47,790
Isn't that missing the point?

517
00:27:50,510 --> 00:27:52,630
Zhao Jiadi,

518
00:27:52,630 --> 00:27:54,720
I'm not here to change your mind,

519
00:27:55,190 --> 00:27:57,310
but to give you a new perspective.

520
00:27:58,790 --> 00:28:00,470
I saw it back at your interview.

521
00:28:01,830 --> 00:28:03,280
You're an idealist.

522
00:28:03,880 --> 00:28:05,470
Risheng isn't your dream company.

523
00:28:06,760 --> 00:28:08,920
I was just like you when I started out.

524
00:28:09,440 --> 00:28:10,830
But now I think,

525
00:28:10,950 --> 00:28:12,190
real maturity

526
00:28:12,470 --> 00:28:15,120
lies in recognizing the shades of gray,

527
00:28:15,670 --> 00:28:17,830
blending in, and accepting it,

528
00:28:18,670 --> 00:28:20,470
then turning it
into your own experience.

529
00:28:21,400 --> 00:28:22,310
Whether you get changed by it,

530
00:28:22,310 --> 00:28:23,470
that's up to your skills.

531
00:28:23,950 --> 00:28:25,350
If you can change it,

532
00:28:27,280 --> 00:28:28,470
that's your vision.

533
00:28:33,150 --> 00:28:34,760
But you're not a full-time hire yet.

534
00:28:35,600 --> 00:28:36,720
You can see it this way,

535
00:28:37,190 --> 00:28:39,470
your probation period
is longer than others,

536
00:28:39,470 --> 00:28:41,120
and the bar is set differently too.

537
00:28:41,760 --> 00:28:43,600
If during probation,

538
00:28:43,760 --> 00:28:46,600
you can't handle your relationship
with your boss.

539
00:28:48,990 --> 00:28:50,280
No matter how talented you are,

540
00:28:50,600 --> 00:28:52,080
Risheng just won't keep you on.

541
00:28:56,920 --> 00:28:58,280
So, what do you think, Zhao Jiadi?

542
00:28:58,470 --> 00:28:59,920
Do you dare to join Risheng?

543
00:28:59,950 --> 00:29:01,400
Will it change you,

544
00:29:01,400 --> 00:29:02,600
or will you change it?

545
00:29:08,830 --> 00:29:09,920
Can I ask something?

546
00:29:10,830 --> 00:29:12,120
Who would be my boss?

547
00:29:12,560 --> 00:29:13,600
Lin Peng, the manager.

548
00:29:14,560 --> 00:29:16,560
The one who kept cutting you off
in the interview.

549
00:29:18,950 --> 00:29:20,400
There's something you should know.

550
00:29:22,470 --> 00:29:23,720
During the meeting,

551
00:29:23,720 --> 00:29:24,880
we all agreed on one thing.

552
00:29:24,880 --> 00:29:25,990
You weren't going to make it.

553
00:29:27,350 --> 00:29:29,120
The only person who spoke up for you

554
00:29:31,400 --> 00:29:32,310
was actually Manager Lin.

555
00:29:44,880 --> 00:29:45,990
Sorry, everyone.

556
00:29:46,560 --> 00:29:47,310
Flush.

557
00:29:48,990 --> 00:29:50,990
Boss, you're on fire today.

558
00:29:50,990 --> 00:29:52,150
All my article fees

559
00:29:52,150 --> 00:29:53,440
